7. An elaboration on the nature of law as a subset of ethics

2
0:00:18,640 --> 0:00:23,440
Value is objective, not intrinsic or subjective. Value is based on and derives from the facts

3
0:00:23,440 --> 0:00:28,480
of reality. It is not derived from mystic authority or from whim, personal or social.

4
0:00:28,480 --> 0:00:32,960
Reality we hold, along with the decision to remain in it, i.e. to stay alive, dictates and demands

5
0:00:32,960 --> 0:00:37,760
the entire code of values. Unlike the lower species, man does not pursue the proper values

6
0:00:37,760 --> 0:00:42,320
automatically. He must discover and choose them, but this does not imply subjectivism.

7
0:00:42,320 --> 0:00:46,880
Every proper value judgement is the identification of a fact. A given object or action advances

8
0:00:46,880 --> 0:00:51,680
man's life. It is good, or it threatens man's life. It is bad, or an evil. The good, therefore,

9
0:00:51,680 --> 0:00:56,880
is a species of the true. It is a form of recognising reality. The evil is a species of the false.

10
0:00:56,880 --> 0:01:01,280
It is a form of contradicting reality. Or, values are a type of fact. They are facts

11
0:01:01,280 --> 0:01:05,680
considered in relation to the choice to live. Existentially, an action of man is good or bad

12
0:01:05,680 --> 0:01:10,240
according to its effect. Its effect is positive or negative on man's life. Thus, creating a

13
0:01:10,240 --> 0:01:15,040
skyscraper is good, and murdering the architect is bad, both by the standard of life. A human

14
0:01:15,040 --> 0:01:18,880
action is not merely physical motion. It is a product of man's ideas and value judgments,

15
0:01:18,880 --> 0:01:22,160
true or false, which themselves drive from a certain kind of mental cause,

16
0:01:22,160 --> 0:01:26,240
ultimately from thought or from evasion. The skyscraper's creator, function on the basis

17
0:01:26,240 --> 0:01:30,080
of proper value judgments and true ideas, including a complex, specialised knowledge.

18
0:01:30,080 --> 0:01:33,920
So you must have expended mental effort, focus, work. So one praises him morally

19
0:01:33,920 --> 0:01:37,760
and admires him. But the murderer acted on ideas of value judgments that defy reality.

20
0:01:37,760 --> 0:01:41,920
So you must have evaded and practised whim worship. So one condemns him morally and despises him.

21
